social_posts.post_text: A thing Ive been doing lately when not drawing has been shooting film. I’ve enjoyed the whole process. Definitely don’t enjoy the price increase. BUT It’s allowed me to see the world differently and to take my time with things. It’s been therapeutic and I hope to pass it down to my kiddos. Anyways. Here’s some film in color.

Dallas beat Phoenix on the road in the season opener, 111-95, behind a team-high 18 points by Raymond Felton. Eight Mavericks scored in double-figures

I’m doing some illustrations with the Mavs this season to highlight some key moments in the team’s history. I’m super excited I was asked to do this.

Dirk made it rain the against the jazz. He scored 29 of his game-high 40 points in the fourth quarter to lead the mavs to a 96-85 comeback win. Dallas trailed by 15 points entering the fourth quarter. It’s the most point scored in a single quarter in franchise history.

OTD (1984) Rolando Blackman and Mark Aguirre scored 30 points each leading the mavs to a 112-105 overtime victory against the hawks.
